  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I ended up implementing this approach, and it incidentally brought a few nice features. Among those, the ability to easily define default state (values) for components, which has been requested for a while. We also have much better state management, which gives our users an easy way to hook into the state of their instantsearch components. This is very useful for routing and/or when using redux to manage your application's state.\n\nAlso, readable current filters 🎉\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1621758/17478760/544c6384-5d6e-11e6-9d86-25cab319ef6d.png)\n",
    "created_at": "2016-08-08T11:50:50Z",
